{'html': '<html>\r\n\r\n<head>\r\n<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">\r\n<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 4.0">\r\n<meta name="ProgId" content="FrontPage.Editor.Document">\r\n<title>Constant Time Queries on Uniformly Distributed Points on a Hemisphere</title>\r\n<meta name="Microsoft Theme" content="willow 011, default">\r\n<meta name="Microsoft Border" content="tl, default">\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n<body background="../../_themes/willow/willbk.jpg" bgcolor="#CCCC99" text="#000000" link="#993333" vlink="#336666" alink="#CC9900"><!--msnavigation--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">\r\n<p>\r\n<applet code="fphover.class" codebase="../../" width="113" height="24">\r\n  <param name="color" value="#000080">\r\n  <param name="hovercolor" value="#0000FF">\r\n  <param name="textcolor" value="#FFFFFF">\r\n  <param name="effect" value="glow">\r\n  <param name="text" value="PhD Students">\r\n  <param name="url" valuetype="ref" value="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/m.slater/research_students.htm">\r\n</applet>\r\n<applet code="fphover.class" codebase="../../" width="120" height="24">\r\n  <param name="color" value="#000080">\r\n  <param name="hovercolor" value="#0000FF">\r\n  <param name="textcolor" value="#FFFFFF">\r\n  <param name="text" value="Projects">\r\n  <param name="effect" value="glow">\r\n  <param name="url" valuetype="ref" value="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/m.slater/projects.htm">\r\n</applet>\r\n<applet code="fphover.class" codebase="../../" width="120" height="24">\r\n  <param name="color" value="#000080">\r\n  <param name="hovercolor" value="#0000FF">\r\n  <param name="textcolor" value="#FFFFFF">\r\n  <param name="text" value="Publications">\r\n  <param name="effect" value="glow">\r\n  <param name="url" valuetype="ref" value="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/m.slater/publications.htm">\r\n</applet>\r\n<applet code="fphover.class" codebase="../../" width="114" height="24">\r\n  <param name="color" value="#000080">\r\n  <param name="hovercolor" value="#0000FF">\r\n  <param name="textcolor" value="#FFFFFF">\r\n  <param name="text" value="Useful Places">\r\n  <param name="effect" value="glow">\r\n  <param name="url" valuetype="ref" value="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/m.slater/useful_places.htm">\r\n</applet>\r\n<applet code="fphover.class" codebase="../../" width="130" height="24">\r\n  <param name="color" value="#000080">\r\n  <param name="hovercolor" value="#0000FF">\r\n  <param name="textcolor" value="#FFFFFF">\r\n  <param name="text" value="VE&amp;Graphics Group">\r\n  <param name="effect" value="glow">\r\n  <param name="url" valuetype="ref" value="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/research/vr">\r\n</applet>\r\n</p>\r\n<!--mstheme--></font></td></tr><!--msnavigation--></table><!--msnavigation--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td valign="top" width="1%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">\r\n\r\n<!--mstheme--></font></td><td valign="top" width="24"></td><!--msnavigation--><td valign="top"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Helvetica">\r\n\r\n<font SIZE="4">\r\n<p ALIGN="CENTER">Constant Time Queries on Uniformly Distributed Points on a\r\nHemisphere</p>\r\n</font>\r\n<p ALIGN="CENTER">Mel Slater</p>\r\n<font SIZE="2">\r\n<p ALIGN="CENTER">Department of Computer Science<br>\r\nUniversity College London, UK</p>\r\n<i>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">A set of uniformly distributed points on a hemisphere is\r\ngenerated using a popular method based on triangle subdivision. In applications,\r\neach data point (for example, representing a direction from a point on a\r\nsurface) is typically associated with additional information (for example, a\r\nradiance value). Given an arbitrary query point on the hemisphere we require the\r\nnearest data point from the given distribution. An algorithm is presented that\r\nfinds the data point in constant time, independently of the number of original\r\npoints in the distribution. A portion of the hemisphere is rendered such that\r\neach point in the distribution has an associated set of quadrilaterals rendered\r\nwith a unique color index for that point. The frame-buffer for the rendered\r\nhemisphere portion can be stored in off-screen memory. Any query point can be\r\n\x91rendered\x92 into this off-screen frame buffer, projected to a \x91pixel\x92\r\nlocation, and the color index stored at this pixel location found. This color\r\nindex is a lookup into an array of the original data points. This algorithm is\r\npresented in detail, and an illustrative implementation in OpenGL is described.</p>\r\n</i><b>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Keywords</p>\r\n</b>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Uniform distribution, sphere, hemisphere, queries,\r\nquery-point</p>\r\n</font>\r\n<p><a href="paper.pdf">Full Paper</a> (PDF)</p>\r\n<p><a href="Code">Software</a>\r\n\r\n<!--mstheme--></font><!--msnavigation--></td></tr><!--msnavigation--></table></body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n',
 'pid': 271,
 'url': 'http://www0.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/M.Slater/Papers/Sphere/index.htm'}